25|$|One factor {{bringing}} on {{the break}} with Metcalf, Wood {{became involved with}} Margaret Behrens (1908–1986), a fairly wealthy realtor and antique dealer, and she moved into Behrens' home in Monroe, Connecticut. Their relationship ended upon Wood's death twenty-seven years later. <b>Wood's</b> <b>ashes</b> were interred in the Behren's plot at Park Cemetery, Bridgeport, Connecticut.|$|R
